RadAssist schema migrations (Alembic)
=====================================

Two schema paths, one set of models (app/models/db_models.py):

  * DEMO / SQLite (zero-config)  — app/db.init_db() calls SQLModel.metadata.create_all
    on first use when DATABASE_URL is set (e.g. sqlite:///./radassist.db). No Alembic
    step is required for the demo. When DATABASE_URL is UNSET the whole DB layer is
    dormant and nothing here runs.

  * REAL DEPLOY / Postgres        — use Alembic so schema changes are versioned and
    reviewable. The baseline migration (versions/70ac64f3c673_*.py) creates the exact
    same three tables create_all would (verified with `alembic check` -> no drift).

The database URL is read from the DATABASE_URL environment variable by alembic/env.py
(alembic.ini's sqlalchemy.url is intentionally blank), so migrations always target the
same database the app does.

Common commands (run from the backend/ directory):

    # apply all migrations to the DB in DATABASE_URL
    DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://user:pass@host:5432/radassist \
        python -m alembic upgrade head

    # after changing app/models/db_models.py, generate the next migration
    DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./radassist.db \
        python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe the change"

    # confirm the DB matches the models (drift check)
    DATABASE_URL=... python -m alembic check

PHI safety: these tables hold auth data (username + scrypt hash + 2FA), a de-identified
image_hash, a pathology label + banded score, and audit rows with a HASHED ip and a
de-identified path. No raw pixels and no patient identifiers are ever stored — keep it
that way when adding columns.
